						               													<description>&amp;quot;Who wants a cup of tea?&amp;quot; one of your friends calls out at a gaming event. This is the starting point of the game, now you need to find out who will be getting up to make it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Next question &amp;quot;Who's in for the tea game?&amp;quot; once the player count is confirmed take two D6, pass them to the starting player (the one who asked for tea) who then rolls the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To stay in the game the starting player has to roll less than '12' on two D6, if successful the dice are passed clockwise to the next player who is then required to roll less than '11' on two D6. The play rotates round the group of players with the number to roll under dropping by '1' each time until someone rolls that number or greater on the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That player is declared the winner of the tea game, given a rousing cheer and sent off to make the tea for all of the other players. Huzzah!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
